
=Description=

"Open Pedagogy: a new paradigm for teaching and learning is an online course offered as part of the U-M Flint Technology in Education: Global Program. It is a two semester course offered for credit to those students enrolled in the Global Program, but also open for anyone interested in the course to contribute to. In the first half of this two semester course, we explore the intersection of education, technology, and an emerging ‘open’ pedagogy. In the second semester, we focus on applying what we have discussed by creating open resources and then working to spread the word about open in our respective communities."
(http://openglobal.wordpress.com/about/)


